    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>halloumi</strong> in half, lengthways (like you're slicing a burger bun!)</p><p>Return the reserved pan with the pepper to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> sliced halloumi</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>peri-peri sauce </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until the halloumi is browned and the reserved pepper is tender – this is your <strong>pepper & peri-peri halloumi</strong></p>",
